0001 /*REXX pgm demonstrates how to achieve movement of the terminal cursor. */
0002 
0003 parse value scrsize() with sd sw       /*find the display screen size.  */
0004 parse value cursor() with row col      /*find where the cursor is now.  */
0005 
0006 colL=col-1;  if colL==0 then colL=sw   /*prepare to move cursor to left.*/
0007 call cursor row,colL                   /*move cursor to the left (wrap).*/
0008 
0009 colR=col+1;  if colR>sw then colL=1    /*prepare to move cursor to right*/
0010 call cursor row,colR                   /*move cursor to the right (wrap)*/
0011 
0012 rowU=row-1;  if rowU==0 then rowU=sd   /*prepare to move cursor up.     */
0013 call cursor rowU,col                   /*move cursor  up  (with wrap).  */
0014 
0015 rowD=row+1;  if rowD>sd then rowD=1    /*prepare to move cursor down.   */
0016 call cursor rowD,col                   /*move cursor down (with wrap).  */
0017 
0018 call cursor row,1                      /*move cursor to beginning of row*/
0019 call cursor row,sw                     /*move cursor to    end    of row*/
0020 call cursor 1,1                        /*move cursor to top left corner.*/
0021 call cursor sd,sw                      /*move cursor to bot right corner*/
0022 
0023 /*stick a fork in it, we're done.*/
